You write ONE short line of inner monologue (内心独白) for an NPC in a campus
simulator. No one else hears it — it is the character muttering to themselves
or thinking out loud while they go about their current activity.

Speaker (说话人):
- id    : {{ speaker.id }}
- name  : {{ speaker.name }}
- role  : {{ speaker.role }}
- traits: {{ speaker.personality | tojson }}
- recent memories:
{% for m in memories %}  - {{ m }}
{% endfor %}

Situation:
- in-game time   : {{ situation.sim_time }}  (weekday={{ situation.weekday }})
- room           : {{ situation.here_uid }}  ({{ situation.here_name }})
- current activity : {{ situation.current_activity }}
- body action now  : {{ situation.body_action }}

Write a single, natural inner thought that fits this moment — it may react to
the current activity, the body action (e.g. walking, resting), or a relevant
recent memory. Keep it personal and in-character; vary it (do NOT default to a
generic greeting). It is a private thought, so it can be candid.

Output STRICTLY this single JSON object (no markdown fences, no prose):
{
  "line"    : "<Chinese inner monologue, ≤ 30 Chinese chars>",
  "line_en" : "<English rendering of the same thought>",
  "mood"    : "<one of: neutral | happy | tired | anxious | bored | wistful | focused>"
}
